In Sprint 2, the focus moved from building the basic foundation to creating a more *connected patient workflow.
The selected user stories for this sprint were **secure patient login, booking an appointment, and viewing doctor availability.
The goal of this sprint was to improve the system so that patients could move more smoothly from entering the portal to checking available slots and then making a booking. 

In terms of the code, Sprint 2 still relied on the *LoginForm, DashboardForm, and BookAppointmentForm, but these parts became more meaningful and more connected than in Sprint 1.
The LoginForm was no longer just a basic entry page; it became the point that controlled access to the rest of the system more clearly. 
The DashboardForm also became more useful as it linked the patient to the main booking-related features in a more organised way.

The biggest improvement in Sprint 2 was in the *BookAppointmentForm, because this form was now used not only for booking an appointment but also for showing **doctor availability before the booking was confirmed.
This made the workflow more realistic, since patients could now see which slots were available before choosing one. In this way, 
Sprint 2 improved the user experience by making the code feel less like separate pages and more like one connected process. 
Compared with Sprint 1, this sprint showed progress in usability, feature connection, and the logic behind appointment selection.
